<subSubSection id="C36CC293FFB9FF9EFF20FDA9FBC5FBE6" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFB9FF9EFF20FDA9FCB3FCE2" blockId="1.[151,1437,474,1293]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFB9FF9EFF20FDA9FEB9FD73" bold="true" box="[199,345,618,644]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Description.</emphasis>
Similar in appearance to other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFB9FF9EFCCEFDA8FC33FD72" authorityName="Zakhvatkin" authorityYear="1953" box="[809,979,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFB9FF9EFCCEFDA8FC33FD72" box="[809,979,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Mongolojassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Male pale yellowish with brown pattern on head, pro-, and mesonotum (
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFB9FF9EFDE5FD4CFDA5FD5E" box="[514,581,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–15" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[201,1385,187,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-16@2.[194,1393,179,1872]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–15. Mongolojassus caucasicus sp. n. (1–14) and M. servadeinus (15). 1―male, dorsal habitus, 2―same, female, 3―pygofer, lateral view, 4―same, ventral view, 5― subgenital plates, valve, connective, styles, and aedeagus, dorsal view, 6–8, 15―aedeagus, back view, 9―same, apical part, 10–12―same, lateral view, 13–14―posterior and lateral view. 15―after D’Urso &amp; Remane, 1994." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480090/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Forewings slightly extending beyond end of abdomen, pale whitish, with some cells partially or entirely bordered with brown or with brown spot occupying part of cell. Brown pattern forms three indistinct transverse stripes at level of mesonotum apex, at middle of clavus, and at its end. Female similar to male, but abdomen reaches beyond ends of forewings (
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFB9FF9EFCE7FD38FCA6FCE2" box="[768,838,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–15" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[201,1385,187,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-16@2.[194,1393,179,1872]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–15. Mongolojassus caucasicus sp. n. (1–14) and M. servadeinus (15). 1―male, dorsal habitus, 2―same, female, 3―pygofer, lateral view, 4―same, ventral view, 5― subgenital plates, valve, connective, styles, and aedeagus, dorsal view, 6–8, 15―aedeagus, back view, 9―same, apical part, 10–12―same, lateral view, 13–14―posterior and lateral view. 15―after D’Urso &amp; Remane, 1994." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480090/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFB9FF9EFF20FCDCFDE7FC1A" blockId="1.[151,1437,474,1293]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">
Pygofer lobes smoothly rounded, with dense groups of long setae in dorsal two thirds (
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFB9FF9EFB45FCDCFAF0FCCE" box="[1186,1296,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–15" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[201,1385,187,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-16@2.[194,1393,179,1872]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–15. Mongolojassus caucasicus sp. n. (1–14) and M. servadeinus (15). 1―male, dorsal habitus, 2―same, female, 3―pygofer, lateral view, 4―same, ventral view, 5― subgenital plates, valve, connective, styles, and aedeagus, dorsal view, 6–8, 15―aedeagus, back view, 9―same, apical part, 10–12―same, lateral view, 13–14―posterior and lateral view. 15―after D’Urso &amp; Remane, 1994." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480090/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Figs. 3–4</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plates rather long, with outer margins twice as long as width of plate at base (
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFB9FF9EFBEFFC80FBAEFCAA" box="[1032,1102,834,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–15" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[201,1385,187,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-16@2.[194,1393,179,1872]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–15. Mongolojassus caucasicus sp. n. (1–14) and M. servadeinus (15). 1―male, dorsal habitus, 2―same, female, 3―pygofer, lateral view, 4―same, ventral view, 5― subgenital plates, valve, connective, styles, and aedeagus, dorsal view, 6–8, 15―aedeagus, back view, 9―same, apical part, 10–12―same, lateral view, 13–14―posterior and lateral view. 15―after D’Urso &amp; Remane, 1994." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480090/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). In back view, aedeagal processes at bases perpendicular to shaft, then bent basad and somewhat diverging, with small additional branches before middles, and with tips bent inwards (
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFB9FF9EFD87FC48FD2BFC51" box="[608,715,907,934]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–15" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[201,1385,187,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-16@2.[194,1393,179,1872]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–15. Mongolojassus caucasicus sp. n. (1–14) and M. servadeinus (15). 1―male, dorsal habitus, 2―same, female, 3―pygofer, lateral view, 4―same, ventral view, 5― subgenital plates, valve, connective, styles, and aedeagus, dorsal view, 6–8, 15―aedeagus, back view, 9―same, apical part, 10–12―same, lateral view, 13–14―posterior and lateral view. 15―after D’Urso &amp; Remane, 1994." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480090/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Figs. 6–8</figureCitation>
). Length of processes exceeds one third of shaft length.Aedeagal shaft not narrowed beyond gonopore (
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFB9FF9EFDABFC6CFD73FC3E" box="[588,659,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–15" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[201,1385,187,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-16@2.[194,1393,179,1872]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–15. Mongolojassus caucasicus sp. n. (1–14) and M. servadeinus (15). 1―male, dorsal habitus, 2―same, female, 3―pygofer, lateral view, 4―same, ventral view, 5― subgenital plates, valve, connective, styles, and aedeagus, dorsal view, 6–8, 15―aedeagus, back view, 9―same, apical part, 10–12―same, lateral view, 13–14―posterior and lateral view. 15―after D’Urso &amp; Remane, 1994." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480090/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
), slightly S-curved in lateral view, with processes almost parallel to distal part of shaft (
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFB9FF9EFE96FC10FE1BFC1A" box="[369,507,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–15" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[201,1385,187,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-16@2.[194,1393,179,1872]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–15. Mongolojassus caucasicus sp. n. (1–14) and M. servadeinus (15). 1―male, dorsal habitus, 2―same, female, 3―pygofer, lateral view, 4―same, ventral view, 5― subgenital plates, valve, connective, styles, and aedeagus, dorsal view, 6–8, 15―aedeagus, back view, 9―same, apical part, 10–12―same, lateral view, 13–14―posterior and lateral view. 15―after D’Urso &amp; Remane, 1994." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480090/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Figs. 10–14</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFB9FF9EFF20FC34FBC5FBE6" blockId="1.[151,1437,474,1293]" box="[199,1061,1015,1042]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">
Body length (in male, including forewings): 
<specimenCount id="9D705A91FFB9FF9EFD5CFC34FD32FBE6" box="[699,722,1015,1041]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
, 2.8–3.0 mm; 
<specimenCount id="9D705A91FFB9FF9EFC93FC34FC69FBE6" box="[884,905,1015,1041]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
, 3.1–3.4 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36CC293FFB9FF9EFF20FBD9FB46FB1E" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFB9FF9EFF20FBD9FB46FB1E" blockId="1.[151,1437,474,1293]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFB9FF9EFF20FBD9FEA2FBC3" bold="true" box="[199,322,1050,1076]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Differs from most other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFB9FF9EFD3DFBD8FC64FBC2" authorityName="Zakhvatkin" authorityYear="1953" box="[730,900,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFB9FF9EFD3DFBD8FC64FBC2" box="[730,900,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Mongolojassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in aedeagal processes with well-developed additional branches. Somewhat similar in this trait to 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFB9FF9EFD28FBFCFCB4FBAE" baseAuthorityName="Horvath" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[719,852,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibiricus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFB9FF9EFD28FBFCFCB4FBAE" box="[719,852,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">M. sibiricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFB9FF9EFC84FBFCFC0CFBAE" box="[867,1004,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–34" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[230,1357,184,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[221,1366,181,1838]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 16–34. Mongolojassus spp. 16–21―M. bicuspidatus (16–19―males from Altai Mts., 20–21―male from North- ern Europe, after Ossiannilsson, 1983), 22–23―M. sibiricus (after Emelyanov, 1964a), 24–31―M. vinokurovi (24–28―males from Irkutsk Oblast, 29–31―male from Yakutia, after Emelyanov, 1976), 32–34―M. elpatjevskii (32–33―female holotype, 34―male paratype). 16, 20, 22, 24–25, 29―aedeagus, posterior view, 19, 28, 31―same, apical part, 17–18, 21, 23, 26–27, 30―same, lateral view, 32, 34―habitus, 33―holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480092/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Figs. 22–23</figureCitation>
), but differs in diverging aedeagal processes (more or less parallel to aedeagal shaft in 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFB9FF9EFD50FBA0FCDCFB8A" baseAuthorityName="Horvath" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[695,828,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibiricus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFB9FF9EFD50FBA0FCDCFB8A" box="[695,828,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">M. sibiricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Most closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFB9FF9EFBBEFBA0FAE5FB8A" baseAuthorityName="Dlabola" baseAuthorityYear="1958" box="[1113,1285,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="servadeinus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFB9FF9EFBBEFBA0FAE5FB8A" box="[1113,1285,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">M. servadeinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFB9FF9EFAF4FBA0FA85FB8A" box="[1299,1381,1122,1149]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–15" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[201,1385,187,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-16@2.[194,1393,179,1872]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–15. Mongolojassus caucasicus sp. n. (1–14) and M. servadeinus (15). 1―male, dorsal habitus, 2―same, female, 3―pygofer, lateral view, 4―same, ventral view, 5― subgenital plates, valve, connective, styles, and aedeagus, dorsal view, 6–8, 15―aedeagus, back view, 9―same, apical part, 10–12―same, lateral view, 13–14―posterior and lateral view. 15―after D’Urso &amp; Remane, 1994." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480090/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
) and similar to it in rather long subgenital plates and aedeagus shape, including long processes with additional branches. Differs from it in narrower aedeagal shaft not narrowed near gonopore and in diverging aedeagal processes almost straight in middle parts (smoothly curved and convergent in distal halves in 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFB9FF9EFC0CFB0CFB76FB1E" baseAuthorityName="Dlabola" baseAuthorityYear="1958" box="[1003,1174,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="servadeinus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFB9FF9EFC0CFB0CFB76FB1E" box="[1003,1174,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">M. servadeinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36CC293FFB9FF9EFF20FB30FAEFFAFA" box="[199,1295,1267,1293]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFB9FF9EFF20FB30FAEFFAFA" blockId="1.[151,1437,474,1293]" box="[199,1295,1267,1293]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFB9FF9EFF20FB30FEAEFAFA" bold="true" box="[199,334,1267,1293]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name derives from the name of the mountain system where it was found.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
